reviewText: Cute little movie. My 2 year old loves it. And its only about 75 minutes long so that helps since their attention span isn't the best sat this age, lol.
No digital copy code and no bonus code none of the normal Disney movie inserts
We love this movie. Weve probably watched it about 50 times with our toddler (not exaggerating) and its still good! Great storyline and humor.
There was no digital copy code

"Planes 2" is a very good movie - just not up to Pixar Studios' usual excellence.  The subject (fire fighting), the supporting characters, and the humor are all top-notch.  The screenplay is professionally written - but just plain predictable.  Still RECOMMENDED.

this is a awesome movie. dusty is back in this amazing sequel to the smash hit. this time dusty hurts himself where he can't race anymore and goes off to be certified as a firefighter to help the fire chief of his home town. disney does it again they make such awesome movies. i can't compare this one to the other they are both good. if you have not seen this movie then i recommend you do. wish they put el chupacabra in this one.
